1.2 – Manuals and Specifications

JavaScript is standardized by ECMA-262, which defines how the language works.
A new version is released every year, and the latest draft is available at tc39.es/ecma262.

Important Resources
MDN Web Docs → Best for everyday learning and examples
https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference

TC39 Proposals → Upcoming JS features (Stage 0–4)
https://github.com/tc39/proposals

Compatibility Tables
https://caniuse.com → Browser support
https://kangax.github.io/compat-table → JS feature support
These resources help developers understand specifications, new features, and browser compatibility.
